EX NO 7(A): :: C PROGRAM TO FIND THE SMALLEST AMONG THREE NUMBERSUSING STRUCTURES


AIM:
To write a program to find smallest among three numbers using structures.

ALGORITHM:
1. Start.
2. Define a variables.
3. Write a program to find the smallest among three numbers using structure.
4. Read the value using scanf.
5. Ask the user to make an input.
6. Print out the answer.
7. End.



PROGRAM:
#include<stdio.h>
struct num
{
int a,b,c;
};
int main()
{
struct num n;
scanf("%d%d%d",&n.a,&n.b,&n.c);
if(n.a<n.b&&n.a<n.c)
{
printf("%d",n.a);
}
else if(n.b<n.a&&n.b<n.c)
{
printf("%d",n.b);
}
else
{printf("%d",n.c);}}

C program to find smallest among three numbers using structures


Developed by:  Prem kumar K
RegisterNumber:  212223060209

INPUT:
113  5  2


OUTPUT:

2

RESULT:
Thus, the program is executed and verified successfully
